    select c.sub_id as sub_id, c.isdn as isdn, c.partition as partition,
    case when n.t_org_charge_month_n <= 0.5*c.t_org_charge_month_n then 1 else 0 end as churn

    left join
    (select sub_id, isdn, partition, t_org_charge_month_n
    from c360
    where partition = {PARTITION_NEXT[i]}) n
    on c.sub_id = n.sub_id and c.isdn = n.isdn
    """
    if i < len(PARTITION_CURR) - 1:
        label_query += "union"
        
print(label_query)

def split_train_valid(df,train_fraction):
    '''
    Down-sample the dataframe by the class
        Params:
            df: dataframe to be splitted
            train_fraction: fraction used for training (0.0 - 1.0)
            class_col: class column name
        Returns:
            train: training set
            valid: validation set
    '''
    train_valid_split_randomized = 'train_valid_split_randomized'
    
    df_rand = df.withColumn(train_valid_split_randomized, F.rand(2021))
    
    train_df = df_rand.filter(f'{train_valid_split_randomized} <= {train_fraction}').drop(train_valid_split_randomized)
    valid_df = df_rand.filter(f'{train_valid_split_randomized} > {train_fraction}').drop(train_valid_split_randomized)
    
    return train_df, valid_df
    
def down_sampling(df, class_col, sampling_ratio):
    '''
    df: dataframe
    class_col: class colname
    sampling_ratio: number of negative samples on 1 positive sample
    '''
    positive_sample = df.filter('{} = 1'.format(class_col))
    negative_sample = df.filter('{} = 0'.format(class_col))
    
    n_positive = positive_sample.count()
    n_negative = negative_sample.count()
    
    n_negative_sample = int(sampling_ratio * n_positive)
    sampling_beta = n_negative_sample/n_negative
    
    (negative_sample_down, negative_sample_leftover) = negative_sample.randomSplit([sampling_beta, 1 - sampling_beta])
    df_out = positive_sample.union(negative_sample_down)
    
    return (df_out, sampling_beta)

def convert_to_pd(df, primary_keys, class_col, prob_col):
    res_df = df.select(primary_keys + [class_col, prob_col]).toPandas()
    res_df['prob'] = res_df[prob_col].apply(lambda x : x[1])
    res_df['label'] = res_df[class_col]
    return res_df[primary_keys + ['prob', 'label']]
    
def print_PR_curve(precision, recall, pr_auc, label, axes, type = 'Train'):
    axes.plot(recall, precision, color='green', label = 'PR curve (area = %0.3f)' % pr_auc, axes =axes)
    axes.plot([0,1], [1,0], 'k--')
    axes.set_ylabel('Precision')
    axes.set_xlabel('Recall')
    axes.set_xlim([0.0, 1.05])
    axes.set_ylim([0.0, 1.05])
    axes.set_title(label + ' Precision-Recall curve '+ type)
    axes.legend(loc='lower right')
    axes.grid(True)
    axes.set_aspect('equal')

def print_PR_curve_with_thresholds(precision, recall, thresholds, label, axes, type = 'Train'):
    axes.plot(thresholds, precision[:-1], 'b--', label='Precision')
    axes.plot(thresholds, recall[:-1], 'g--', label='Recall')
    axes.set_xlabel('Threshold')
    axes.legend(loc='center right')
    axes.set_title(label + ' precision-recall curve '+ type)
    axes.set_ylim([0, 1])
    axes.grid(True)

def print_ROC_curve(fpr, tpr, roc_auc, label, axes, type = 'Train'):
    axes.plot(fpr, tpr, color='green', label='ROC curve (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc, axes =axes)
    axes.plot([0,1], [0,1], 'k--')

# cumulative_gains
def cumulative_gains(df, label_col, score_col):
    '''Calculate cumulative gains 
    df: original sample dataframe with label and score
    label_col: column name of label
    score_col: column name of score
    '''
    sorted_df = df.sort_values(by=score_col, ascending=False)
    sample_no = len(df)
    gain_df = pd.DataFrame()
    gain_df['Index'] = range(0, 11)
    customer_per_range = sample_no//(len(gain_df)-1)
    total_respons = sorted_df[label_col].sum()
    total_non_respons = sample_no - total_respons
    cumulative_respond = []
    cumulative_non_respond=[]
    for idx in range(0,11):
        #print(idx)
        res = 100.0 * sorted_df[label_col][: idx * customer_per_range].sum()/total_respons
        non_res = 100.0 * ((idx * customer_per_range) - res/100.0)/total_non_respons
        cumulative_respond.append(res)
        cumulative_non_respond.append(non_res)
    gain_df['Index'] = gain_df['Index'].apply(lambda x: x * 10)
    gain_df['Res_rate_raw'] = cumulative_respond
    gain_df['NonRes_rate_raw'] = cumulative_non_respond
    return gain_df

# print_cumulative_gains
def print_cumulative_gains(gain_df, label, axes):
    axes.plot(gain_df['Index'], gain_df['Res_rate_raw'], color='green', label='Model')
    for i, j in zip(gain_df['Index'], gain_df['Res_rate_raw']):
        axes.annotate(str(builtins.round(j,1)) + '%', xy=(i,j + 1))
    axes.plot(gain_df['Index'], gain_df['Index'], color='black', label='Random')
    axes.set_ylabel('% responders reached')
    axes.set_xlabel('Decile (% of customer)')
    axes.set_title('Cumulative Gains chart ' + label + ' set')
    axes.legend(loc='lower right')
    axes.grid(True)
    
# lift_chart
def lift_chart(df, label_col, score_col):
    valid_df_pd = df.sort_values(by=score_col, ascending=False)
    sample_no = len(valid_df_pd)
    positive_no = valid_df_pd[label_col].sum()
    lift_df = pd.DataFrame()
    lift_df['Index'] = range(1, 101)
    customer_per_range = sample_no//len(lift_df)
    normed_res_rate = positive_no/sample_no
    response_rate_raw = []
    response_rate_normed = []
    for idx in range(1,101):
        res = valid_df_pd[label_col][(idx-1)* customer_per_range : idx * customer_per_range].sum()/customer_per_range
        response_rate_raw.append(res)
        response_rate_normed.append(res/normed_res_rate)
    lift_df['Res_rate_raw'] = response_rate_raw
    lift_df['Res_rate_norm'] = response_rate_normed
    lift_df['Random'] = 1
    return lift_df
    
# print_lift
def print_lift(lift_df, label, axes):
    axes.plot(lift_df['Index'], lift_df['Res_rate_norm'], color='green', label='Model')
    axes.plot(lift_df['Index'], lift_df['Random'], color='red', label='Random')
    axes.set_ylabel('Lift @ decile')
    axes.set_xlabel(label + ' Decile (% of customer)')
    axes.legend(loc='upper right')
    axes.grid(True)
